to the editor re study suggests overuse of chemotherapy near life 's end news article may 13 the study of the overuse of chemotherapy is an important insight into the treatment of cancer as a former director of child psychiatry at memorial sloan kettering cancer center i am familiar with the overuse of chemotherapy often the reason for the overuse of chemotherapy is the oncologist 's feeling of helplessness in trying to save the patient 's life by continuing chemotherapy the oncologist conveys to the patient that there is hope for a cure oncology is one of the most difficult medical professions because it can evoke a feeling in patients that the doctor will prevent death a mission that is often impossible yehuda nir md new york may 14 2001

